{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859760613,"sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","part":{"id":"prt_d797d70d2001HJ2AhVusZkAIk7","messageID":"msg_d797d3504001T0jky0pmUMyhzT","sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - Same repository: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see sandbox-orchestration design for `go.mod` and versions).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n8: \n9: ### Config\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: const LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n13: \n14: type Config struct {\n15:     Port                  string\n16:     Debug                 bool\n17:     EnableTLS             bool\n18:     TLSCert               string\n19:     TLSKey                string\n20:     MaxConcurrentRequests int  // 0 = unlimited at flag level; NewServer coerces to 1000\n21: }\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ### CLI flags (`cmd/router/main.go`)\n25: \n26: | Flag | Default |\n27: |------|---------|\n28: | `-port` | `8080` |\n29: | `-enable-tls` | `false` |\n30: | `-tls-cert` | `\"\"` |\n31: | `-tls-key` | `\"\"` |\n32: | `-debug` | `false` |\n33: | `-max-concurrent-requests` | `1000` (0 means unlimited per flag help; `NewServer` still sets default 1000 when `<= 0`) |\n34: \n35: ### Server struct\n36: \n37: ```go\n38: type Server struct {\n39:     config         *Config\n40:     engine         *gin.Engine\n41:     httpServer     *http.Server\n42:     sessionManager SessionManager\n43:     storeClient    store.Store\n44:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n45:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n46: }\n47: ```\n48: \n49: - `httpTransport`: `IdleConnTimeout: 0`, `DisableCompression: false`.\n50: - Store: `store.Storage()` for both session manager and `storeClient`.\n51: - Gin mode: `DebugMode` if `config.Debug`, else `ReleaseMode`.\n52: \n53: ### Route table\n54: \n55: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n56: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n57: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n58: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n59: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `gin.Logger`, `gin.Recovery`, `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n60: | POST | same | same | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n61: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n62: | POST | same | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n63: \n64: ### SessionManager interface\n65: \n66: ```go\n67: type SessionManager interface {\n68:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### manager implementation (`session_manager.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type manager struct {\n76:     storeClient     store.Store\n77:     workloadMgrAddr string\n78:     httpClient      *http.Client\n79: }\n80: ```\n81: \n82: - `NewSessionManager(storeClient store.Store) (SessionManager, error)` reads `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required).\n83: - HTTP client: `Timeout: 2 * time.Minute`; transport `MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 100`, `DisableCompression: false`; `http2.ConfigureTransports` with `ReadIdleTimeout: 30s`, `PingTimeout: 15s`.\n84: - Endpoints: `AgentRuntime` → `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`; `CodeInterpreter` → `.../v1/code-interpreter`.\n85: - Request: `Content-Type: application/json`; optional `Authorization: Bearer` from `loadWorkloadManagerAuthToken()` reading `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` (trimmed); missing file → no header (warning if non-NotExist error).\n86: \n87: ### JWT (`jwt.go`)\n88: \n89: **Constants (unexported unless noted):**\n90: \n91: | Name | Value |\n92: |------|--------|\n93: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` |\n94: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` |\n95: | `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` |\n96: | `PrivateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` |\n97: | `PublicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` |\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // init: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n101: ```\n102: \n103: **JWTManager:**\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type JWTManager struct {\n107:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n108:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n109:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n110: }\n111: ```\n112: \n113: - `NewJWTManager()`: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)`.\n114: - `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)`:\n115:   - Base claims: `exp` = now+jwtExpiration (Unix), `iat` = now (Unix), `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`.\n116:   - Merges custom claims (e.g. `session_id`).\n117:   - Signing: `jwt.SigningMethodRS256`, signed with RSA private key.\n118: \n119: **Algorithm:** RS256  \n120: **Key type:** RSA 2048-bit, PKCS1 private key PEM (`RSA PRIVATE KEY`), PKIX public key PEM (`PUBLIC KEY`).\n121: \n122: **TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx):**\n123: \n124: - If `clientset == nil`, try `rest.InClusterConfig()`; on failure log warning and return nil (ephemeral keys).\n125: - Else build Secret `IdentitySecretName` in `IdentityNamespace`, type `Opaque`, labels `app=agentcube`, `component=router`, data `private.pem` + `public.pem`.\n126: - Create; on `AlreadyExists`, Get secret and `loadPrivateKeyPEM`.\n127: \n128: ### Reverse proxy\n129: \n130: - `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)`; `proxy.Transport = s.httpTransport`.\n131: - Director: sets `req.URL.Path` to normalized path, clears `RawPath`, `req.Host = targetURL.Host`, forwarding headers, `Authorization` if JWT non-empty.\n132: - `ModifyResponse`: sets `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n133: - No per-request timeout wrapper (commented-out context timeout in source).\n134: \n135: ### Concurrency middleware\n136: \n137: - Buffered channel size `config.MaxConcurrentRequests`.\n138: - `select`: send to channel or `default` → 429 + abort.\n139: \n140: ### Health JSON shapes\n141: \n142: - Live: `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`.\n143: - Ready OK: `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`.\n144: - Ready fail: `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"session manager not available\"}`.\n145: \n146: ### Error helper (`handleGetSandboxError`)\n147: \n148: - If `apierrors.APIStatus`: use `Status().Code` if non-zero; message from status or `err.Error()`; if code is 500, replace message with `internal server error`; respond `gin.H{\"error\": message}`.\n149: - Else 500 `{\"error\":\"internal server error\"}`.\n150: \n151: ### Environment variables\n152: \n153: | Variable | Used by |\n154: |----------|---------|\n155: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Session manager (required) |\n156: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | JWT secret namespace (optional, default `default`) |\n157: \n158: ### Dependencies (direct use in router)\n159: \n160: - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`, `golang.org/x/net/http2`, `k8s.io/api`, `k8s.io/apimachinery`, `k8s.io/client-go`, `k8s.io/klog/v2`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`.\n\n(End of file - total 160 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- Same repository: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see sandbox-orchestration design for `go.mod` and versions).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n\n### Config\n\n```go\nconst LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int  // 0 = unlimited at flag level; NewServer coerces to 1000","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md","time":{"start":1775859760592,"end":1775859760611}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859760616,"sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","part":{"id":"prt_d797d79bf00104php5x2jLxkiG","messageID":"msg_d797d3504001T0jky0pmUMyhzT","sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package store\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"context\"\n21: \t\"errors\"\n22: \t\"time\"\n23: \n24: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n25: )\n26: \n27: // ErrNotFound is returned when a session is not found in the store.\n28: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n29: \n30: // Store defines the interface for session storage backends.\n31: // Implementations include Redis and Valkey providers.\n32: type Store interface {\n33: \t// Ping checks connectivity to the store.\n34: \tPing(ctx context.Context) error\n35: \n36: \t// GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox information by session ID.\n37: \t// Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n38: \tGetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n39: \n40: \t// StoreSandbox stores sandbox information in the store.\n41: \tStoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n42: \n43: \t// UpdateSandbox updates existing sandbox information.\n44: \tUpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n45: \n46: \t// DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox from the store.\n47: \tDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n48: \n49: \t// ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes that have expired before the given time.\n50: \tListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n51: \n52: \t// ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes inactive since before the given time.\n53: \tListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n54: \n55: \t// UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n56: \tUpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n57: \n58: \t// Close closes the store connection.\n59: \tClose() error\n60: }\n\n(End of file - total 60 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go","time":{"start":1775859760601,"end":1775859760614}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859760627,"sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","part":{"id":"prt_d797d75330011aaYFjT7icX5xi","messageID":"msg_d797d3504001T0jky0pmUMyhzT","sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package types\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"time\"\n21: )\n22: \n23: // SandboxInfo contains information about a sandbox instance.\n24: // This type is used across the agentcube system for session management and routing.\n25: type SandboxInfo struct {\n26: \t// Kind is the resource kind (e.g., \"AgentRuntime\", \"CodeInterpreter\")\n27: \tKind string `json:\"kind\"`\n28: \n29: \t// SandboxID is the unique identifier for the sandbox\n30: \tSandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n31: \n32: \t// SandboxNamespace is the Kubernetes namespace where the sandbox runs\n33: \tSandboxNamespace string `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n34: \n35: \t// Name is the name of the runtime resource\n36: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n37: \n38: \t// EntryPoints define how to access the sandbox\n39: \tEntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n40: \n41: \t// SessionID is the unique session identifier\n42: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n43: \n44: \t// CreatedAt is when the sandbox was created\n45: \tCreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n46: \n47: \t// ExpiresAt is when the sandbox expires\n48: \tExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n49: \n50: \t// Status is the current status of the sandbox (e.g., \"Running\", \"Pending\")\n51: \tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n52: \n53: \t// PodIP is the IP address of the sandbox pod\n54: \tPodIP string `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n55: \n56: \t// PodName is the name of the sandbox pod\n57: \tPodName string `json:\"podName,omitempty\"`\n58: }\n59: \n60: // SandboxEntryPoint defines an access point to the sandbox.\n61: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n62: \t// Path is the URL path prefix for this entry point\n63: \tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n64: \n65: \t// Protocol is the communication protocol (e.g., \"http\", \"https\")\n66: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n67: \n68: \t// Endpoint is the host:port address\n69: \tEndpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n70: }\n71: \n72: // CreateSandboxRequest is sent to the Workload Manager to create a new sandbox.\n73: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n74: \t// Kind is the type of sandbox to create\n75: \tKind string `json:\"kind\"`\n76: \n77: \t// Name is the name of the runtime resource\n78: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n79: \n80: \t// Namespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n81: \tNamespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n82: }\n83: \n84: // CreateSandboxResponse is received from the Workload Manager after creating a sandbox.\n85: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n86: \t// SessionID is the unique session identifier\n87: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n88: \n89: \t// SandboxID is the unique sandbox identifier\n90: \tSandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n91: \n92: \t// Name is the name of the runtime resource\n93: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n94: \n95: \t// Namespace is the Kubernetes namespace\n96: \tNamespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n97: \n98: \t// EntryPoints define how to access the sandbox\n99: \tEntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n100: \n101: \t// Status is the initial status of the sandbox\n102: \tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n103: }\n104: \n105: // EntryPoint is an alias for SandboxEntryPoint for backward compatibility.\n106: // Deprecated: Use SandboxEntryPoint instead.\n107: type EntryPoint = SandboxEntryPoint\n\n(End of file - total 107 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage types\n\nimport (\n\t\"time\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go","time":{"start":1775859760598,"end":1775859760625}}}}
