{"type":"text","timestamp":1775860187792,"sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","part":{"id":"prt_d7981ab8a001Y7sar5xQpvhTxO","messageID":"msg_d79810132001GT8a7RY4L4Vwsp","sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","type":"text","text":"If","time":{"start":1775860187789,"end":1775860187789}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860187835,"sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","part":{"id":"prt_d79810dd1001K5AYiTvxr6wva9","messageID":"msg_d79810132001GT8a7RY4L4Vwsp","sessionID":"ses_286835f93ffelyzrAay21blODp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-010 Design: Router Session Management\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-010  \n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\nThe Router Session Management component provides comprehensive session lifecycle management for the AgentCube Router. It serves as the bridge between incoming HTTP requests and sandbox instances, integrating with the Kubernetes API via client-go to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, maintaining session state in the session store, and ensuring proper session affinity for routing.\n\nThe Session Manager handles four primary responsibilities:\n1. **Session Resolution**: Maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints using the session store with fallback to Kubernetes resource lookup\n2. **Session Lifecycle**: Manages session creation, updates, expiration, and cleanup through the store interface\n3. **Session Affinity**: Ensures consistent routing of requests to the same sandbox instance within a session\n4. **Resource Integration**: Uses client-go to interact with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       External API Clients                                   │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\n│  │  Web UI     │  │   CLI Tool  │  │  Agent SDK  │                         │\n│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\n└─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Router Layer (AR-009)                                │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                    Session Management Layer                             │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ SessionResolver │  │ SessionManager  │  │   AffinityRouter       │ │ │\n│  │  │ · Resolve       │  │ · Create        │  │ · Sticky Routing       │ │ │\n│  │  │ · Cache Lookup  │  │ · Refresh       │  │ · Endpoint Index       │ │ │\n│  │  │ · K8s Fallback  │  │ · Terminate     │  │ · Health Check         │ │ │\n│  │  └────────┬────────┘  └────────┬────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  │           │                    │                                      │ │\n│  │  ┌────────▼────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────┐  │ │\n│  │  │              Session Lifecycle Manager                          │  │ │\n│  │  │  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐ │  │ │\n│  │  │  │ Create        │  │ Expire        │  │ Cleanup Worker      │ │  │ │\n│  │  │  │ · WorkloadMgr │  │ · TTL Check   │  │ · Async cleanup     │ │  │ │\n│  │  │  │ · Store       │  │ · Activity    │  │ · Retry logic       │ │  │ │\n│  │  │  └───────────────┘  └───────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘ │  │ │\n│  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                │                    │                       │\n                ▼                    ▼                       ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Integration Layer                                       │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Session Store   │  │  K8s Client-go   │  │  Workload Manager        │  │\n│  │  (Redis/Valkey)  │  │  (AR-003)        │  │  (AR-004/005)            │  │\n│  │                  │  │                  │  │                          │  │\n│  │  · Get/Set       │  │  · AgentRuntime  │  │  · Sandbox Creation      │  │\n│  │  · TTL           │  │  · CodeInterpreter│  │  · Status Polling        │  │\n│  │  · Expiration    │  │  · Watch/Inform  │  │  · Entry Points          │  │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Session Resolution Flow\n\n```\nIncoming Request\n   │\n   ├──▶ Extract x-agentcube-session-id header\n   │\n   ▼\nSessionManager.Resolve\n   │\n   ├──▶ sessionID empty? ──Yes──▶ Create new session ──┐\n   │         │                                          │\n   │         No                                         │\n   │         │                                          │\n   │         ▼                                          │\n   │    Query session store by ID                       │\n   │         │                                          │\n   ├──▶ Found? ──Yes──▶ Update activity ──▶ Return info │\n   │         │                                          │\n   │         No                                         │\n   │         │                                          │\n   │         ▼                                          │\n   │    Check K8s resource exists?                      │\n   │         │                                          │\n   ├──▶ Exists? ──Yes──▶ Create new session ────────────┤\n   │         │                                          │\n   │         No                                         │\n   │         │                                          │\n   │         ▼                                          │\n   │    Return error (resource not found)               │\n   │                                                    │\n   └──▶ Session Creation ◀──────────────────────────────┘\n            │\n            ├──▶ Call Workload Manager /v1/{kind}\n            ├──▶ Wait for sandbox ready\n            ├──▶ Store session in store\n            └──▶ Return SessionInfo\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **SessionManager** | Main session lifecycle orchestrator | Context, sessionID, RuntimeReference | SessionInfo or error |\n| **SessionResolver** | Resolves sessions with caching and fallback | SessionID, namespace, name, kind | SandboxInfo or error |\n| **AffinityRouter** | Sticky session routing | SessionID | EndpointEntry |\n| **LifecycleManager** | Background session maintenance | Stop channel, config | Cleanup operations |\n| **RuntimeClient** | K8s CRD operations | Context, reference | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| **Store** | Session persistence | Context, session data | Confirmation |\n| **Metrics** | Observability | Operation results | Prometheus metrics |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── doc.go                      # Package documentation\n├── config.go                   # Router configuration (existing)\n├── server.go                   # HTTP server (existing AR-009)\n├── jwt.go                      # JWT management (existing AR-009)\n├── session_manager.go          # SessionManager interface and implementation\n├── session_resolver.go         # Session resolution with caching\n├── session_lifecycle.go        # Session creation, expiration, cleanup\n├── session_affinity.go         # Sticky routing and endpoint indexing\n├── session_types.go            # Session-specific type definitions\n├── session_metrics.go          # Prometheus metrics\n├── k8s_client.go               # Kubernetes client-go wrapper\n└── handlers.go                 # HTTP handlers (extends AR-009)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### SessionManager Interface\n\n```go\n// SessionManager handles the complete lifecycle of sessions.\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    // Resolve resolves a session ID to sandbox information.\n    // Creates a new session if not found and createIfMissing is true.\n    Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, runtimeRef RuntimeReference, createIfMissing bool) (*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // Create creates a new session for the given runtime.\n    Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // Refresh updates session activity timestamp and extends TTL.\n    Refresh(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    \n    // Terminate ends a session and triggers sandbox cleanup.\n    Terminate(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    \n    // Get retrieves session information by ID.\n    Get(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // ListActive returns all active sessions with optional filtering.\n    ListActive(ctx context.Context, filter SessionFilter) ([]*SessionInfo, error)\n    \n    // StartLifecycleManager starts background maintenance goroutines.\n    StartLifecycleManager(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n}\n\n// SessionResolver provides cached session resolution with fallback.\ntype SessionResolver interface {\n    // GetSandboxBySession resolves session to sandbox with store + K8s fallback.\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    \n    // WarmCache preloads frequently accessed sessions.\n    WarmCache(ctx context.Context, namespace string) error\n}\n```\n\n#### SessionInfo\n\n```go\n// SessionInfo contains all information about an active session.\ntype SessionInfo struct {\n    // SessionID is the unique session identifier (UUID v4)\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    \n    // SandboxID links to the sandbox instance\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    \n    // RuntimeRef identifies the source runtime resource\n    RuntimeRef RuntimeReference `json:\"runtimeRef\"`\n    \n    // Status is the current session status\n    Status SessionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n    \n    // CreatedAt is when the session was created\n    CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    \n    // LastActivity is when the session was last accessed\n    LastActivity time.Time `json:\"lastActivity\"`\n    \n    // ExpiresAt is when the session will expire\n    ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    \n    // EntryPoints cache for routing (copied from SandboxInfo)\n    EntryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n}\n\n// SessionStatus represents the state of a session.\ntype SessionStatus string\n\nconst (\n    SessionStatusPending    SessionStatus = \"Pending\"\n    SessionStatusActive     SessionStatus = \"Active\"\n    SessionStatusExpiring   SessionStatus = \"Expiring\"\n    SessionStatusTerminated SessionStatus = \"Terminated\"\n)\n\n// RuntimeReference identifies a runtime resource.\ntype RuntimeReference struct {\n    Kind      string // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    Name      string\n    Namespace string\n}\n\n// SessionFilter provides filtering options for ListActive.\ntype SessionFilter struct {\n    Status      SessionStatus\n    RuntimeKind string\n    Namespace   string\n    Before      time.Time // Created before\n}\n```\n\n#### SessionManager Implementation\n\n```go\n// sessionManager implements SessionManager.\ntype sessionManager struct {\n    // store provides session persistence\n    store store.Store\n    \n    // k8sClient provides access to AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs\n    k8sClient *RuntimeClient\n    \n    // workloadMgrAddr is the Workload Manager endpoint for sandbox creation\n    workloadMgrAddr string\n    \n    // httpClient for Workload Manager communication\n    httpClient *http.Client\n    \n    // config holds session management configuration\n    config *SessionConfig\n    \n    // metrics for session operations\n    metrics *sessionMetrics\n    \n    // affinityRouter for sticky session routing\n    affinityRouter *AffinityRouter\n}\n\n// SessionConfig holds session management configuration.\ntype SessionConfig struct {\n    // DefaultTTL is the default session time-to-live (default: 30m)\n    DefaultTTL time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxTTL is the maximum allowed session TTL (default: 24h)\n    MaxTTL time.Duration\n    \n    // CleanupInterval is how often to run expired session cleanup (default: 5m)\n    CleanupInterval time.Duration\n    \n    // ActivityTimeout is the duration after which an inactive session expires (default: 30m)\n    ActivityTimeout time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n#### AffinityRouter\n\n```go\n// AffinityRouter provides sticky session routing.\ntype AffinityRouter struct {\n    // sessionIndex maps session IDs to sandbox endpoints\n    sessionIndex map[string]*EndpointEntry\n    \n    // mu protects sessionIndex\n    mu sync.RWMutex\n    \n    // metrics for routing operations\n    metrics *sessionMetrics\n}\n\n// EndpointEntry represents a routable endpoint for a session.\ntype EndpointEntry struct {\n    SessionID   string\n    SandboxID   string\n    Endpoint    string\n    LastUsed    time.Time\n    Healthy     bool\n}\n\n// GetEndpoint returns the endpoint for a session, updating last used time.\nfunc (r *AffinityRouter) GetEndpoint(sessionID string) (*EndpointEntry, bool)\n\n// RegisterSession adds a new session to the affinity index.\nfunc (r *AffinityRouter) RegisterSession(sessionInfo *SessionInfo)\n\n// UnregisterSession removes a session from the affinity index.\nfunc (r *AffinityRouter) UnregisterSession(sessionID string)\n\n// HealthCheck marks endpoint health status.\nfunc (r *AffinityRouter) HealthCheck(sessionID string, healthy bool)\n```\n\n#### RuntimeClient (Kubernetes Integration)\n\n```go\n// RuntimeClient provides typed access to runtime CRDs via client-go.\ntype RuntimeClient struct {\n    client    runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n    informers externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n}\n\n// NewRuntimeClient creates a Kubernetes client for runtime CRDs.\nfunc NewRuntimeClient(config *rest.Config) (*RuntimeClient, error)\n\n// GetAgentRuntime retrieves an AgentRuntime resource by namespace/name.\nfunc (c *RuntimeClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\n// GetCodeInterpreter retrieves a CodeInterpreter resource by namespace/name.\nfunc (c *RuntimeClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n\n// WatchAgentRuntimes returns a watch interface for AgentRuntime changes.\nfunc (c *RuntimeClient) WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n\n// WatchCodeInterpreters returns a watch interface for CodeInterpreter changes.\nfunc (c *RuntimeClient) WatchCodeInterpreters(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (watch.Interface, error)\n\n// ResolveRuntime looks up runtime configuration from K8s CRDs.\nfunc (c *RuntimeClient) ResolveRuntime(ctx context.Context, ref RuntimeReference) (*RuntimeConfig, error)\n```\n\n### Request/Response Types\n\n```go\n// CreateSessionRequest represents a request to create a new session.\ntype CreateSessionRequest struct {\n    RuntimeRef RuntimeReference `json:\"runtimeRef\" validate:\"required\"`\n    TTL        time.Duration    `json:\"ttl,omitempty\"` // Optional custom TTL\n}\n\n// CreateSessionResponse represents the response from session creation.\ntype CreateSessionResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string                    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID   string                    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    Status      SessionStatus             `json:\"status\"`\n    EntryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n    ExpiresAt   time.Time                 `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n}\n\n// SessionListResponse contains a list of sessions.\ntype SessionListResponse struct {\n    Sessions []*SessionInfo `json:\"sessions\"`\n    Total    int            `json:\"total\"`\n}\n\n// TerminateSessionResponse represents the result of session termination.\ntype TerminateSessionResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    Terminated  bool      `json:\"terminated\"`\n    TerminatedAt time.Time `json:\"terminatedAt,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\n// Default configuration values\nconst (\n    DefaultSessionTTL         = 30 * time.Minute\n    MaxSessionTTL             = 24 * time.Hour\n    DefaultCleanupInterval    = 5 * time.Minute\n    DefaultActivityTimeout    = 30 * time.Minute\n    DefaultHTTPTimeout        = 2 * time.Minute\n    SessionIDHeader           = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n)\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n    ErrorCodeSessionNotFound     = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrorCodeSessionExpired      = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n    ErrorCodeRuntimeNotFound     = \"RUNTIME_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrorCodeSandboxCreateFailed = \"SANDBOX_CREATE_FAILED\"\n    ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID    = \"INVALID_SESSION_ID\"\n    ErrorCodeSessionConflict     = \"SESSION_CONFLICT\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Session Manager Methods\n\n#### Resolve\n\n```go\nfunc (m *sessionManager) Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, runtimeRef RuntimeReference, createIfMissing bool) (*SessionInfo, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. If `sessionID` is empty and `createIfMissing` is true, create new session\n2. Query session store by ID\n3. If found, update activity and return SessionInfo\n4. If not found, check if K8s resource exists\n5. If exists and `createIfMissing`, create new session\n6. If resource not found, return `ErrRuntimeNotFound`\n\n**Error Conditions:**\n- Store unavailable: `ErrSessionStoreUnavailable`\n- Resource not found: `ErrRuntimeNotFound`\n- Sandbox creation failed: `ErrSandboxCreateFailed`\n\n#### Create\n\n```go\nfunc (m *sessionManager) Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error)\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Generate new UUID v4 session ID\n2. Call Workload Manager to create sandbox\n3. Wait for sandbox ready status\n4. Store session in session store with TTL\n5. Register in affinity router\n6. Return SessionInfo\n\n**Example:**\n```go\nsessionInfo, err := sessionMgr.Create(ctx, RuntimeReference{\n    Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n    Name:      \"my-agent\",\n    Namespace: \"default\",\n})\n```\n\n#### Refresh\n\n```go\nfunc (m *sessionManager) Refresh(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Retrieve session from store\n2. Update last activity timestamp\n3. Extend expiration (capped at MaxTTL from creation)\n4. Update store entry\n\n**Error Conditions:**\n- Session not found: `ErrSessionNotFound`\n- Session expired: `ErrSessionExpired`\n- Store unavailable: wrapped store error\n\n#### Terminate\n\n```go\nfunc (m *sessionManager) Terminate(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n1. Mark session as terminating in affinity router\n2. Delete session from store\n3. Call Workload Manager to delete sandbox\n4. Unregister from affinity router\n5. Record metrics\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\n// SessionError represents session management errors.\ntype SessionError struct {\n    Code    string\n    Message string\n    Cause   error\n}\n\nfunc (e *SessionError) Error() string { return e.Message }\nfunc (e *SessionError) Unwrap() error { return e.Cause }\n\n// Sentinel errors\nvar (\n    ErrSessionNotFound         = &SessionError{Code: ErrorCodeSessionNotFound, Message: \"session not found\"}\n    ErrSessionExpired          = &SessionError{Code: ErrorCodeSessionExpired, Message: \"session has expired\"}\n    ErrRuntimeNotFound         = &SessionError{Code: ErrorCodeRuntimeNotFound, Message: \"runtime resource not found\"}\n    ErrSandboxCreateFailed     = &SessionError{Code: ErrorCodeSandboxCreateFailed, Message: \"failed to create sandbox\"}\n    ErrInvalidSessionID        = &SessionError{Code: ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID, Message: \"invalid session ID format\"}\n    ErrSessionConflict         = &SessionError{Code: ErrorCodeSessionConflict, Message: \"session already exists\"}\n    ErrSessionStoreUnavailable = &SessionError{Code: \"STORE_UNAVAILABLE\", Message: \"session store unavailable\"}\n)\n```\n\n### Error Mapping\n\n| Error | HTTP Status | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n|-------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ErrSessionNotFound` | 404 | No | Return 404 with suggestion |\n| `ErrSessionExpired` | 401 | No | Return 401, suggest re-authentication |\n| `ErrRuntimeNotFound` | 404 | No | Return 404, resource deleted |\n| `ErrSandboxCreateFailed` | 500 | Yes | Log error, return 500 |\n| `ErrSessionConflict` | 409 | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n| `ErrSessionStoreUnavailable` | 503 | Yes | Return 503, retry logic |\n| K8s API errors | 500/503 | Varies | Map using apierrors package |\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n```go\n// Handler-level error handling\nfunc (h *Handler) handleSessionResolve(c *gin.Context) {\n    sessionID := c.GetHeader(SessionIDHeader)\n    runtimeRef := extractRuntimeRef(c)\n    \n    sessionInfo, err := h.sessionMgr.Resolve(c.Request.Context(), sessionID, runtimeRef, true)\n    if err != nil {\n        h.handleSessionError(c, err)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Continue with routing...\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleSessionError(c *gin.Context, err error) {\n    switch {\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrSessionNotFound):\n        h.respondError(c, 404, ErrorCodeSessionNotFound, \"Session not found\", nil)\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrSessionExpired):\n        h.respondError(c, 401, ErrorCodeSessionExpired, \"Session expired, please re-authenticate\", nil)\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrRuntimeNotFound):\n        h.respondError(c, 404, ErrorCodeRuntimeNotFound, \"Runtime resource not found\", nil)\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrSessionStoreUnavailable):\n        h.respondError(c, 503, \"STORE_UNAVAILABLE\", \"Session store temporarily unavailable\", nil)\n    default:\n        h.respondError(c, 500, \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", \"Internal server error\", err)\n    }\n}\n\n// Kubernetes error mapping\nfunc mapK8sError(err error) error {\n    if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        return ErrRuntimeNotFound\n    }\n    if apierrors.IsTimeout(err) {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSessionStoreUnavailable, err)\n    }\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"kubernetes API error: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSessionManager_Resolve(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name            string\n        sessionID       string\n        runtimeRef      RuntimeReference\n        createIfMissing bool\n        mockStore       func() *mockStore\n        mockK8s         func() *mockK8sClient\n        expectedError   error\n        expectedStatus  SessionStatus\n    }{\n        {\n            name:            \"resolve_existing_session\",\n            sessionID:       \"sess-abc-123\",\n            runtimeRef:      RuntimeReference{Kind: \"AgentRuntime\", Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n            createIfMissing: false,\n            mockStore: func() *mockStore {\n                s := &mockStore{}\n                s.On(\"GetSandboxBySessionID\", mock.Anything, \"sess-abc-123\").\n                    Return(&types.SandboxInfo{\n                        SessionID: \"sess-abc-123\",\n                        Status:    \"Running\",\n                    }, nil)\n                s.On(\"UpdateSessionLastActivity\", mock.Anything, \"sess-abc-123\", mock.Anything).\n                    Return(nil)\n                return s\n            },\n            expectedStatus: SessionStatusActive,\n        },\n        {\n            name:            \"create_new_session_when_not_found\",\n            sessionID:       \"\",\n            runtimeRef:      RuntimeReference{Kind: \"AgentRuntime\", Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n            createIfMissing: true,\n            mockStore:       func() *mockStore { return &mockStore{} },\n            expectedStatus:  SessionStatusActive,\n        },\n        {\n            name:            \"error_when_runtime_not_found\",\n            sessionID:       \"sess-xyz-789\",\n            runtimeRef:      RuntimeReference{Kind: \"AgentRuntime\", Name: \"missing\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n            createIfMissing: false,\n            mockStore: func() *mockStore {\n                s := &mockStore{}\n                s.On(\"GetSandboxBySessionID\", mock.Anything, \"sess-xyz-789\").\n                    Return(nil, store.ErrNotFound)\n                return s\n            },\n            mockK8s: func() *mockK8sClient {\n                c := &mockK8sClient{}\n                c.On(\"GetAgentRuntime\", mock.Anything, \"default\", \"missing\").\n                    Return(nil, apierrors.NewNotFound(schema.GroupResource{}, \"missing\"))\n                return c\n            },\n            expectedError: ErrRuntimeNotFound,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Setup mocks and execute test\n        })\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestSessionManager_Create(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name           string\n        runtimeRef     RuntimeReference\n        mockWorkload   func() *mockWorkloadClient\n        expectedError  bool\n        expectedStatus SessionStatus\n    }{\n        {\n            name:       \"create_agentruntime_session\",\n            runtimeRef: RuntimeReference{Kind: \"AgentRuntime\", Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n            mockWorkload: func() *mockWorkloadClient {\n                c := &mockWorkloadClient{}\n                c.On(\"CreateSandbox\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).\n                    Return(&types.CreateSandboxResponse{\n                        SessionID: \"new-session\",\n                        SandboxID: \"sb-123\",\n                        Status:    \"Running\",\n                        EntryPoints: []types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n                            {Protocol: \"http\", Endpoint: \"10.0.0.1:8080\"},\n                        },\n                    }, nil)\n                return c\n            },\n            expectedStatus: SessionStatusActive,\n        },\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n\nfunc TestAffinityRouter_GetEndpoint(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name           string\n        sessionID      string\n        setupRouter    func() *AffinityRouter\n        expectedFound  bool\n        expectedEndpoint string\n    }{\n        {\n            name:      \"existing_session\",\n            sessionID: \"sess-123\",\n            setupRouter: func() *AffinityRouter {\n                r := NewAffinityRouter()\n                r.RegisterSession(&SessionInfo{\n                    SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n                    EntryPoints: []types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n                        {Protocol: \"http\", Endpoint: \"10.0.0.1:8080\"},\n                    },\n                })\n                return r\n            },\n            expectedFound:    true,\n            expectedEndpoint: \"http://10.0.0.1:8080\",\n        },\n        {\n            name:           \"nonexistent_session\",\n            sessionID:      \"sess-missing\",\n            setupRouter:    func() *AffinityRouter { return NewAffinityRouter() },\n            expectedFound:  false,\n        },\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n\nfunc TestRuntimeClient_GetAgentRuntime(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name          string\n        namespace     string\n        name          string\n        expectedError error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:      \"get_existing_runtime\",\n            namespace: \"default\",\n            name:      \"my-agent\",\n            // ...\n        },\n        {\n            name:          \"runtime_not_found\",\n            namespace:     \"default\",\n            name:          \"missing\",\n            expectedError: ErrRuntimeNotFound,\n        },\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSessionLifecycle_Integration(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup test environment with fake K8s and in-memory store\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    \n    // Create session\n    sessionInfo, err := sessionMgr.Create(ctx, RuntimeReference{\n        Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n        Name:      \"test-agent\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    })\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.NotEmpty(t, sessionInfo.SessionID)\n    assert.Equal(t, SessionStatusActive, sessionInfo.Status)\n    \n    // Resolve session\n    resolved, err := sessionMgr.Resolve(ctx, sessionInfo.SessionID, RuntimeReference{\n        Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n        Name:      \"test-agent\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    }, false)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, sessionInfo.SessionID, resolved.SessionID)\n    \n    // Refresh session\n    err = sessionMgr.Refresh(ctx, sessionInfo.SessionID)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Terminate session\n    err = sessionMgr.Terminate(ctx, sessionInfo.SessionID)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Verify session is gone\n    _, err = sessionMgr.Get(ctx, sessionInfo.SessionID)\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrSessionNotFound)\n}\n\nfunc TestSessionExpiration_Integration(t *testing.T) {\n    // Create session with short TTL\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    config := &SessionConfig{\n        DefaultTTL:      100 * time.Millisecond,\n        CleanupInterval: 50 * time.Millisecond,\n    }\n    \n    sessionMgr := NewSessionManagerWithConfig(mockStore, mockK8s, config)\n    stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n    go sessionMgr.StartLifecycleManager(stopCh)\n    defer close(stopCh)\n    \n    sessionInfo, err := sessionMgr.Create(ctx, RuntimeReference{\n        Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n        Name:      \"test\",\n        Namespace: \"default\",\n    })\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Wait for expiration\n    time.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\n    \n    // Session should be expired\n    _, err = sessionMgr.Get(ctx, sessionInfo.SessionID)\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrSessionExpired)\n}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Requirements\n\n| Component | Coverage Target | Critical Paths |\n|-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n| SessionManager | >85% | Create, Resolve, Refresh, Terminate |\n| SessionResolver | >80% | Cache hit, fallback, error paths |\n| AffinityRouter | >80% | Register, unregister, concurrent access |\n| RuntimeClient | >75% | Get, Watch, error mapping |\n| Lifecycle Manager | >75% | Cleanup, expiration handling |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Direct Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Local | Session store interface |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Local | SandboxInfo and types |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client for runtime CRDs |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.x | Session ID generation |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API client |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s API machinery |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics collection |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n\n### Client-Go Integration\n\nThe RuntimeClient uses the generated client-go library from `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n)\n\n// Create typed client\nruntimeClient := runtimev1alpha1.NewForConfigOrDie(config)\n\n// Create informer factory\ninformerFactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 10*time.Minute)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Required | Workload Manager endpoint for sandbox creation |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `default` | Namespace for JWT secrets and resources |\n| `SESSION_DEFAULT_TTL` | `30m` | Default session time-to-live |\n| `SESSION_MAX_TTL` | `24h` | Maximum allowed session TTL |\n| `SESSION_CLEANUP_INTERVAL` | `5m` | Expired session cleanup interval |\n| `SESSION_ACTIVITY_TIMEOUT` | `30m` | Inactivity timeout for sessions |\n\n### Default Configuration Table\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `DefaultTTL` | 30m | Default session time-to-live |\n| `MaxTTL` | 24h | Maximum allowed session TTL |\n| `CleanupInterval` | 5m | Expired session cleanup interval |\n| `ActivityTimeout` | 30m | Inactivity timeout for sessions |\n\n---\n\n## Metrics\n\n### Prometheus Metrics\n\n```go\nvar (\n    sessionCreations = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_session_creations_total\",\n            Help: \"Total session creations by kind and result\",\n        },\n        []string{\"kind\", \"result\"},\n    )\n    \n    activeSessions = prometheus.NewGauge(\n        prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_active_sessions\",\n            Help: \"Current number of active sessions\",\n        },\n    )\n    \n    sessionsExpired = prometheus.NewCounter(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_sessions_expired_total\",\n            Help: \"Total sessions expired\",\n        },\n    )\n    \n    sessionResolveDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentcube_session_resolve_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"Session resolution duration\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        },\n        []string{\"cache_hit\"},\n    )\n    \n    sessionDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n        prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentcube_session_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"Total session lifetime duration\",\n            Buckets: []float64{60, 300, 600, 1800, 3600, 7200, 86400},\n        },\n    )\n    \n    affinityRouteHits = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n        prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentcube_affinity_route_hits_total\",\n            Help: \"Total affinity router hits by result\",\n        },\n        []string{\"result\"},\n    )\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Session Creation Flow\n\n```go\nfunc (m *sessionManager) Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error) {\n    // Generate new session ID\n    sessionID := uuid.New().String()\n    \n    // Build Workload Manager request\n    endpoint := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/v1/%s\", m.workloadMgrAddr, mapKindToEndpoint(runtimeRef.Kind))\n    reqBody := types.CreateSandboxRequest{\n        Kind:      runtimeRef.Kind,\n        Name:      runtimeRef.Name,\n        Namespace: runtimeRef.Namespace,\n    }\n    \n    // Call Workload Manager\n    resp, err := m.callWorkloadManager(ctx, endpoint, reqBody)\n    if err != nil {\n        m.metrics.sessionCreations.WithLabelValues(runtimeRef.Kind, \"failed\").Inc()\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Build session info\n    now := time.Now()\n    sessionInfo := &SessionInfo{\n        SessionID:    sessionID,\n        SandboxID:    resp.SandboxID,\n        RuntimeRef:   runtimeRef,\n        Status:       SessionStatusActive,\n        CreatedAt:    now,\n        LastActivity: now,\n        ExpiresAt:    now.Add(m.config.DefaultTTL),\n        EntryPoints:  resp.EntryPoints,\n    }\n    \n    // Persist to store\n    sandboxInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n        Kind:             runtimeRef.Kind,\n        SandboxID:        resp.SandboxID,\n        SandboxNamespace: runtimeRef.Namespace,\n        Name:             runtimeRef.Name,\n        EntryPoints:      resp.EntryPoints,\n        SessionID:        sessionID,\n        CreatedAt:        now,\n        ExpiresAt:        sessionInfo.ExpiresAt,\n        Status:           resp.Status,\n    }\n    \n    if err := m.store.StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxInfo); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to store session: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Register in affinity router\n    m.affinityRouter.RegisterSession(sessionInfo)\n    \n    m.metrics.sessionCreations.WithLabelValues(runtimeRef.Kind, \"success\").Inc()\n    m.metrics.activeSessions.Inc()\n    \n    return sessionInfo, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Background Lifecycle Management\n\n```go\nfunc (m *sessionManager) StartLifecycleManager(stopCh <-chan struct{}) {\n    // Cleanup ticker for expired sessions\n    cleanupTicker := time.NewTicker(m.config.CleanupInterval)\n    defer cleanupTicker.Stop()\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-cleanupTicker.C:\n            m.cleanupExpiredSessions(context.Background())\n        case <-stopCh:\n            return\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (m *sessionManager) cleanupExpiredSessions(ctx context.Context) error {\n    expiredSandboxes, err := m.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), 100)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list expired sandboxes: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    for _, sandbox := range expiredSandboxes {\n        // Terminate session\n        if err := m.Terminate(ctx, sandbox.SessionID); err != nil {\n            klog.Errorf(\"Failed to terminate expired session %s: %v\", sandbox.SessionID, err)\n            continue\n        }\n        \n        m.metrics.sessionsExpired.Inc()\n        m.metrics.activeSessions.Dec()\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Session Routing Design](session-routing/design.md) — Router design details\n- [Session Routing Specification](session-routing/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [client-go library spec](deployment/client-go.md) — Generated client details\n- [AR-009](changes/AR-009/design.md) — Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n- [AR-005](changes/AR-005/design.md) — Sandbox Creation Handler\n- [Kubernetes client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go) — Official Go client\n- [client-go informers](https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go/informers) — Caching and watching resources\n\n---\n\n*AR-010 — Module: pkg/router — Language: Go — Size: M*\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/doc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/design.md","time":{"start":1775860187796,"end":1775860187831}}}}
